<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Skeletons on Luke Jaeger</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/tags/skeletons/</link><description>Recent content in Skeletons on Luke Jaeger</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://trickfilm.github.io/tags/skeletons/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Late Again (This Bus Goes To A&amp;S)</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/late-again-this-bus-goes-to-a+s/</link><pubDate>Tue, 28 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/late-again-this-bus-goes-to-a+s/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Even death has to wait when the bus is late.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
I built the steel structure in &lt;a href="https://cad.onshape.com/documents/0d04830c3e9a07993e9ffff0/w/ef87bed257ce441c68d4160d/e/46adf5aa0b4f6faa5964491a?renderMode=0&amp;amp;uiState=69f0e03ddc49c9557dbd93cc"&gt;OnShape CAD&lt;/a&gt;, based approximately on the &lt;a href="https://www.alamy.com/this-green-steel-arch-supports-the-125th-st-station-on-the-new-york-city-subway-irt-1-train-located-at-the-intersection-of-125th-street-and-broadway-image383489306.html"&gt;Manhattan Valley Viaduct&lt;/a&gt;, then manually traced it and laser-cut the holes.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Incident At Pelvis</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/incident-at-pelvis/</link><pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/incident-at-pelvis/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This week we started a war for no reason. And my back hurts.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Skeletub, Skelephone, Skelemelon</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/skeletub-skelephone-skelemelon/</link><pubDate>Sun, 07 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/skeletub-skelephone-skelemelon/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Scene Of The Crime (Who Do You Think You Are?)</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/scene-of-the-crime-who-do-you-think-you-are/</link><pubDate>Sun, 20 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/scene-of-the-crime-who-do-you-think-you-are/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Bitter and sweet childhood memories superimposed. In the summer of 1971, a 45 of &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EJ-4cKFVC34"&gt;&amp;ldquo;Mr. Big Stuff&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt; played on a neighbor&amp;rsquo;s portable record player at a picnic in the park. The skeleton getting kicked in the face is me, a few years later, during a fool&amp;rsquo;s mission to deliver block-association leaflets to the neighbors. &amp;ldquo;Who do you think you are&amp;rdquo; is a question I remember being asked more than once; perhaps that&amp;rsquo;s why the song made such an impression.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
I&amp;rsquo;ve been making an ongoing effort to use more secondary colors in my palette. This was an early step in that process. I&amp;rsquo;m also drawn to ambiguous colors like in the elevated tracks. Is that green or orange? Yes!&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Giant Sloth</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/giant-sloth-photocomp/</link><pubDate>Sun, 23 Feb 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/giant-sloth-photocomp/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;I heard you like skeletons, so here&amp;rsquo;s a big one!&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Trixie With Powerlines</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/trixie-with-powerlines/</link><pubDate>Sun, 12 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/trixie-with-powerlines/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Skeleton Crew At The Hospital (For Lisa)</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/skeleton-crew-at-the-hospital-for-lisa/</link><pubDate>Thu, 28 Nov 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/skeleton-crew-at-the-hospital-for-lisa/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Skeleton Driver</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/skeleton-driver/</link><pubDate>Wed, 21 Aug 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/skeleton-driver/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Skulls and Spraypaint</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/skulls-and-spraypaint/</link><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/skulls-and-spraypaint/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Iron Man And Friends</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/iron-man-and-friends/</link><pubDate>Mon, 21 Aug 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/iron-man-and-friends/</guid><description/></item><item><title>To Get To The Other Side</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/to-get-to-the-other-side/</link><pubDate>Sun, 21 May 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/to-get-to-the-other-side/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Death Rides For Free</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/death-rides-woodcut/</link><pubDate>Sun, 31 Jan 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/death-rides-woodcut/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Made during a lovely afternoon workshop at Oaxaca&amp;rsquo;s radical printmaking collective &lt;a href="https://www.instagram.com/subterraneos.oax"&gt;Subterraneos&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Busy Skeletons</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/busy-skeletons/</link><pubDate>Mon, 11 Jan 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/busy-skeletons/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Postage Stamps | Skulls</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/postage-stamps-skulls/</link><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/postage-stamps-skulls/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Sedlec Ossuary, Kutna Hora, Czech Republic</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/sedlec-ossuary-kutna-hora-czech-republic/</link><pubDate>Fri, 16 Jun 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/sedlec-ossuary-kutna-hora-czech-republic/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sedlec_Ossuary"&gt;This ossuary&lt;/a&gt; contains the bones of somewhere between 40,000 and 70,000 people. It is perhaps the most metal tourist attraction anywhere. In fact, while we were there, a traveling metal band pulled up in their tour bus for a visit!&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>An Agent Will Inform You When Your Mask Is No Longer Necessary</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/an-agent-will-inform-you-when-your-mask-is-no-longer-necessary/</link><pubDate>Fri, 21 Apr 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/an-agent-will-inform-you-when-your-mask-is-no-longer-necessary/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Skeleton Funnies</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/skeleton-funnies/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Jan 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/skeleton-funnies/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Carolina Shout</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/carolina-shout/</link><pubDate>Sun, 15 May 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/carolina-shout/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Another in a series of “antique music videos,” set to a 1921 composition by jazz pioneer &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_P._Johnson"&gt;James P. Johnson&lt;/a&gt;, an originator of the Harlem Stride piano style. The animation reflects the multi-leveled, over-the-top delight and frantic silliness of this amazing musical performance.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
In bringing these old musical treasures to new audiences I hope to recreate in some small way the experience of hearing this music for the first time.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>3 Levels</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/3-levels/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Jan 2013 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/3-levels/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Fish And Skulls Under Old Washington Street El, Boston, 1985</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/fish-and-skulls-under-old-washington-street-el-boston-1985/</link><pubDate>Sun, 20 Feb 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/fish-and-skulls-under-old-washington-street-el-boston-1985/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Good old &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I2GZrEhYyT40"&gt;Harry The Greek&amp;rsquo;s&lt;/a&gt;, where I got my first pair of safety shoes. &lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
In the background: Dudley Station on the old Orange Line elevated line. The platforms were made of wood, and a &amp;ldquo;Let&amp;rsquo;s Make Every Day Safe Driving Day&amp;rdquo; billboard, featuring a &lt;a href="https://i.pinimg.com/originals/56/13/99/561399a883ee46ae8931506b3db157e2.jpg"&gt;likeness of Eisenhower&lt;/a&gt;, remained remarkably intact 30+ years on, probably because its location directly over the tracks made it vandal-proof.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
The photo was taken during a big sewer main upgrade project which turned loose an unbelievable number of rats.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Death Rides The IRT</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/death-rides-the-irt/</link><pubDate>Sat, 01 Jan 2005 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/death-rides-the-irt/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Bone Tower</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/bone-tower/</link><pubDate>Sat, 27 Apr 2002 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/bone-tower/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Skeletrain With Tube And Pills</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/skeletrain-with-tube-and-pills/</link><pubDate>Sat, 27 Apr 2002 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/skeletrain-with-tube-and-pills/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Bone Bridge</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/bone-bridge/</link><pubDate>Tue, 01 Jan 2002 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/bone-bridge/</guid><description/></item><item><title>3 Running Characters</title><link>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/3-running-characters/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 1990 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://trickfilm.github.io/art/3-running-characters/</guid><description/></item></channel></rss>